sources.title: Square Dance Jubilee (1949) Musical, Western | Full Length Movie
sources.description:
Two talent scouts for a New York-based country music TV show called "Square Dance Jubilee" are sent out West to get authentic western singing acts. They find what they're looking for, but also get mixed up in cattle rustling and murder.

Director: Paul Landres
Writers: William L. Nolte, Ron Ormond, Daniel B. Ullman
Stars: Don 'Red' Barry, Mary Beth Hughes, Wally Vernon

metadata.Plot: In the early days of television, Don Blake and partner Sam are sent west to look for musicians and singers for the TV show Square Dance Jubilee. In their search they run into a gang of rustlers that change brands and then sell the cattle. The gang plans their next raid when the whole county is in town for the TV broadcast of the local talent. But Don and Sam are on to the rustlers and are ready.
metadata.Writer: William L. Nolte, Ron Ormond, Daniel B. Ullman
